Foot & mouth disease - UK 20010220.0325
Foot & mouth disease - UK (12) 20010301.0407
[1
Date: 1 Mar 2001
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Asia Daily News, 1 Mar 2001 [edited
<http://asia.dailynews.yahoo.com/headlines/world/article.html?s=asia/headlines/010301/world/afp/Foot-and-mouth_disease_confirmed_at_another_British_site__six_more_expected.html>

A new outbreak of FMD was confirmed in Britain and 6 more were expected to
be confirmed later in the day, it was announced. The confirmed site was in
Cumbria, northwest England.
Chief Veterinary Officer Jim Scudamore said the other 6 outbreaks expected
to be confirmed later were in Northern Ireland, 2 in Scotland, and 3 more
in England.
Northern Ireland's agriculture ministry said it believed the disease had
crossed the Irish Sea to the province. If all the sites are confirmed it
will bring the number of outbreaks in Britain to 33.
